Source-Makefile: feeds/packages/net/addrwatch/Makefile
Build-Depends: USE_MUSL:argp-standalone

Package: addrwatch
Version: 1.0.2-3
Depends: +libc +USE_GLIBC:librt +USE_GLIBC:libpthread +libpcap +libevent2
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Section: net
Category: Network
Repository: base
Title: IPv4/IPv6 and ethernet address pairing tool
Maintainer: Ondrej Caletka <ondrej@caletka.cz>
Source: addrwatch-1.0.2.tar.gz
License: GPL-3.0-or-later
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Type: ipkg
Description:   This is a tool similar to arpwatch. It main purpose is to monitor network and
  log discovered ethernet/ip pairings. Addrwatch is extremely useful in networks
  with IPv6 autoconfiguration (RFC4862) enabled. It allows to track IPv6
  addresses of hosts using IPv6 privacy extensions (RFC4941).

  This contains the main addrwatch program.
https://github.com/fln/addrwatch
Ondrej Caletka <ondrej@caletka.cz>
@@

